Perfect! Let’s integrate the thumbnail-ready MQTT listener into the startup script so after a reboot, one command launches the whole system: OpenClaw gateway, MQTT monitor, and the listener with automatic image resizing.

Step 1 — Updated startup script

Create or edit start_openclaw_system.sh:

cd ~/device_manager
nano start_openclaw_system.sh

Paste the following:

#!/bin/bash
# start_openclaw_system.sh
# Starts OpenClaw gateway, MQTT monitor, and MQTT listener (with thumbnail resizing)

# -------------------------
# CONFIG
# -------------------------
OPENCLAW_CLI="$HOME/.npm-global/bin/openclaw"
VENV_PATH="$HOME/device_manager/venv"
MQTT_TOPIC="home/camera/#"
LISTENER="$HOME/device_manager/mqtt_listener.py"

# -------------------------
# 1. Start OpenClaw Gateway
# -------------------------
echo "Starting OpenClaw gateway..."
$OPENCLAW_CLI --dev gateway --force &  # runs in background
sleep 3  # give it a few seconds to start

# -------------------------
# 2. Start MQTT monitor (mosquitto_sub) in a separate terminal
# -------------------------
echo "Starting MQTT monitor on $MQTT_TOPIC..."
gnome-terminal -- bash -c "mosquitto_sub -h localhost -t '$MQTT_TOPIC' -v; exec bash" &

# -------------------------
# 3. Activate Python venv and run mqtt_listener.py
# -------------------------
echo "Starting MQTT listener (thumbnail-ready)..."
source $VENV_PATH/bin/activate
python $LISTENER
Step 2 — Make the script executable
chmod +x start_openclaw_system.sh
Step 3 — Run the script
./start_openclaw_system.sh

OpenClaw gateway starts in background

MQTT monitor opens in a new terminal for debugging

mqtt_listener.py starts in the current terminal, listening for events and resizing snapshots automatically

✅ After reboot workflow

